items.name: Saturday Morning Cartoons
items.description:
This LoRA was trained on 112 images and is meant to emulate American-style cartoon images, similar to the kinds of cartoons you may have seen on TV every Saturday morning back in the day.

It works really well with this checkpoint:
ReV Animated

I haven't tried it with a lot of other checkpoints, but I think it's best to use it with models or checkpoints that are already meant to produce non-photographic images.

Prompting:

If using ReV Animated, placing ((masterpiece)), ((highest quality)), and ((detailed)) in front of the prompt is useful, however you can remove ((detailed)) or lower the weight and it seems to produce flatter/simpler images.

The appropriate LoRA weight seems to be between 0.4 and 0.7. At around 0.8 I notice things get a little weird. But please experiment with this. Lower weights will be subtle but still affect the output.

Triggers for the LoRA are 'saturdaymorning' and 'cartoon'. You can use one of them or both of them, or neither. If you use both words, the LoRA will be stronger at lower weights. With only one of the trigger words or neither of them, you can push the weight higher.

See sample images for prompting examples.

And I have been using these negative embeddings:

EasyNegative

Deep Negative

bad_prompt_version2

bad-artist

bad-artist-anime

items.name: Fertilization for Inpainting
items.description:
I am a deviant gentleman of culture. I haven't been able to reliable add fertilization x-rays to my images(all the LORAs are crap). So my thought process went like this. What if I make a LORA for inpainting and manufacture a clean dataset? Well this is the LORA for inpainting. Only remains to make a shitload of poses with different characters and inpainting on them to make a good dataset for the concept LORA(but that is for the future).

First of all check the instructions in the version Tab!

Edit: 20230526: finished the concept LORA, if you don't need it for inpainting use that instead.

Edit (hopefully final) 20230524 : Finished a stylized heart shaped impregnation LOCON. Seems to have good repeatability and seems rather reliable. With that one V4.1 I consider this project done and will move back to character LORAs and to doing a generalist impregnation LORA(which will likely be in the 4.1 style). Sadly reliability increases with the version so the first ones might be iffy.

The LORAS specialize as following:

  • V1, V2 and V3(192 and 512) for a semi 3d cropped style.

  • V3(128) and V4(Locon) for a semi stylized ovum surrounded style.

  • V4.1(Locon) stylized heart in the nucleus style.

Edit (Again) 20230523 : Once again cleaned and simplified the dataset, this time tried making it a LOCON to see if i could catch more details. I was able to make it more reliable as long as it is a spherical cow in space or a mostly round or square inpaint mask of the appropriate size.

I have another Iteration in the works but this particular project has me a bit burnt out.

BTW: Leave me a review and some feedback will you! This was a lot of work.

Ignore the crossed out stuff Below. I just finished V3 in 3 sizes 128, 192 and 512.

I recommend to take the following precautions:

  • Use the LORA which more closely matches the available space

  • 192 seems to be an evil resolution(even if it is a multiple of 64), it you are going to use it remember to set the inpaint area to only masked and set the resolution to 192x192(it won't change the size of your image but will only pay attention to that area)

  • Using a wrongly sized LORa works but if the Lora is for a smaller resolution the image will be smaller or maybe repeated. If the Lora is bigger, the in painted part will be extra large and cropped.

  • Use denoising strength = 1 Anything below that has given me subpar results.

  • I recommend to use latent noise or latent nothing. Other setting work but YMMV.

  • Setting the inPaint area to only masked helps with distortion.

  • The lora seems stable in all the range but it is a bit hard to know if it is overfit due to it being rather simplistic.

  • Either use 128 or 512 unless you really need something in the middle then make sure to follow the suggestion for 192.

  • Check the color images I added to see more or less how big the inpaint image will look. Red is 128, Blue is 192, green is 256 and Yellow is 512.

I pretty much restarted from scratch removing from my dataset all the speech bubbles(as i was unable to control their alignment). Also rotated everything to reduce orientation bias.

Also added the 128 size LORA as that size is a lot easier to inpaint, as it is sometimes hard to find a larger space.

In the gallery i will add the originals and the inpainted versions of the examples.

I'll add the dataset as it might be useful in the future, also the tag summary but i doubt that one will be useful as i pruned most of it as they were false positives.

I seem to get good results using: <lora:fertilization:1>, fertilization, ovum, (sperm_cell:1.2)

Use latent noise or latent nothing otherwise the existing stuff will get on the way. I recommend to use it at denoise 1, if you want to lower it to get transparency YMMV.

Also be mindful of the space you give it, if it too small it might omit something.

*Edit: if you use it in a full image it works like a weird background.

*Edit2: Working on a V2, will probably consolidate everything under Fertilization as depending on the inpaint shape you can get both ovum and sperm or just one of them which can get annoying specially for batch inpaints. My other gripe is the size of the stuff in the inpaint, If I am not convinced with V2, I will tweak the dataset to make the images take less space of the training area to see if I can get it to try to be more compact.

modelVersions.name: v4.1 Heart Locon 128x128
modelVersions.description:
Abandon variety embrace repeatability!

A stylized version using a heart shaped ovum. Mostly a synthetic dataset. Has high repeatability and reliability as long as the inpaint space is symmetrical.

Requires the following:

  • I like it most at .95 strength(why? I don't know, but i think there's more sperm at 1 which overloads the image a bit.)

  • a symmetric inpaint area

  • Latent Nothing

  • Only masked

  • padding pixels: 0

  • Width and and height: calculate what you want by looking at the colored pictures and match it to your available inpaint area then copy the written resolution from the image that looks the best to you.

  • For the guide images: Red is 128, Blue is 192, green is 256 and Yellow is 512.

  • Denoise strenght:1

  • Mask transparency 0 or better yet use your own mask file.

  • Check the attached configuration screenshot if you have a doubt.

This is totally different to the other ones with a dataset created from scratch. I thought that maybe i should post it separately but nah!

I finally happy with this one. It is likely the end product. I will use it to make a synthetic dataset for a generalized fertilization LORA in the future.

modelVersions.name: v4.0 Locon 128x128
modelVersions.description:
I have attained repeatability but at what cost?

Warning: This version is a LOCON

Requires the following:

  • a circle or square with the approximate 128 pix of diameter or side

  • Latent Nothing

  • Only masked

  • padding pixels: 0

  • Width and and height either image size or 128x128

  • Denoise strenght:1

  • Mask transparency 0 or better yet use your own mask file. I added the mask file together with the original image(before inpainting) in the gallery.

After this I once again started from scratch I am thinking about going for the simpler stylized "heart in the middle" style with a mostly synthetic dataset. My dream of an automatic impregnation Lora seems to be going further as even if i manage to make a good synthetic dataset how well will the speech bubbles be repeated if I am having so much trouble with repeatability in inpaint?

modelVersions.name: v3.0 Small 128x128
modelVersions.description: This seems to be the most useful one due to it's size.

modelVersions.name: v3.0 Medium 192x192
modelVersions.description: This one is a bit problematic SD seems to dislike this resolution. Make sure to set inpainting area to only masked and set the height and width to 192.

modelVersions.name: v3.0 Big 512x512
modelVersions.description: Lora trained on 512x512 images. If you are inpainting in a image before upscaling the result might be too big. only use it if you have a lot of free space to inpaint in your image.

modelVersions.name: v2.0 192x192 dataset
modelVersions.description:
This is actually V4 but then again 2 and 3 while not bad were not a great improvement. To train this I modified the dataset to be 192x192. This way I was able to regularize the size of the image in the in painting zone. On the other hand if the zone is too big you might get duplicates or weird stretching. If there's demand I might try to make a 256 version. V1 is of course 512.

I might give this another try doing adding vertical flip as i saw some bias. I am not sure about the speech bubbles of some of the dataset as they often appear pointing the wrong way(as expected).

I recommend to use:

  • Try to make the impaint area close to 192x192 or if smaller try making it either round or square.

  • Lora Weight: 1

  • imprint area: only masked

  • Denoising strength: 1

items.name: Sukabu Style [Android Girls Edition]
items.description:
Makes android girls in similar style of Sukabu.

How to use
Start prompting with the usual "1girl" then I recommend using one or more of "android", "robot joints", "mechanical parts" and other android related tags.
Recommended settings for NAI is ~0.8 LoRA strength with Euler A sampler and for AOM2 ~1 LoRA strength with DPM++ 2M Karras. Make sure to use "3D" and "realistic" in negatives on AOM2 and other models with realism mixed in otherwise the style might be too washed out. Or just use NAI or another model with good support for drawing styles.

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!
Like my LoRAs and want more? Please consider a small tip towards my electricity bill and further training >.<

MISC
Trained on NAI with dataset of ~180 images. The dataset contained a lot of very detailed images of android-y deformed non-human content which couldn't be removed since, well, there wouldn't be much left, so you likely have to be a bit more precise with your prompts.

SD1.5 Pruned emaonly モデルをトレーニングのベースとして使用します。ステップ数が少なく、画面の調整にのみ適しており、調整ツールとして使用できます。

鍵はモデルとプロンプト入力にあります。 2.5Dおよび3Dキャラクターモデルでの使用を推奨します。 このローラには VAE がありません。

英語は上手ではありませんが、ご容赦ください。 合計 20 のバージョンがあり、より汎用性の高い 2 つのバージョンが選択されています（V15-Pruned-emaonly_tifa_v1 および V15-Pruned-emaonly_tifa_v2）。 具体的な効果は実際に映像を走らせてみないと分かりません。 Lora の重量をより高い価格に調整しましたが、重量が低いほど調整効果はわかりにくくなります。 Lora の推奨体重: 約 0.6 ～ 1。

初心者は独自の Lora モデルを作成しようとしています。サポートしてください。質問がある場合は、下のコメント領域にメッセージを残してください。

商用利用は禁止です。個人学習交流利用、商用利用は個人的にご連絡ください。

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

Use the SD1.5 Pruned emaonly model as the basis for training, the number of steps is small, it is only suitable for adjusting the screen, it can be used as an adjustment tool Lora!

The key lies in your Models and Prompt input. It is recommended to use it with 2.5D and 3D character models. This Lora does not have VAE.

English is not good, please forgive. There are a total of 20 versions, and the two versions with better generalization are selected（V15-Pruned-emaonly_tifa_v1 & V15-Pruned-emaonly_tifa_v2）. The specific effect can only be known by running the picture. I have adjusted the weight of Lora to a higher price, and the lower the weight, the less obvious the adjustment effect will be. Lora weight suggestion: about 0.6-1.

Newcomers are trying to make their own Lora models, please support, and please leave a message in the comment area below if you have any questions.

Commercial use is not allowed, personal learning exchange use, commercial use please contact me privately.

Thanks.

items.name: Zest [Shinmai Maou no Keiyakusha / The Testament of Sister New Devil ]
items.description:
Zest from Shinmai Maou no Keiyakusha AKA The Testament of Sister New Devil

How to use
Just use the trigger tag "zste" along with "1girl". Her horns can be added with the custom tag "zhorns". Beyond that her collar is tagged as "spiked collar" and the maid outfit brooch as, well, "brooch".

Default outfit:
1girl, zste, solo, black leotard, center opening, shoulder armor, black elbow gloves, white pants, black boots, long sleeves, zhorns,

Due to the low amount of useable screencaps and most of the images showing Zest in her default outfit this LoRA took a lot of effort and tweaking to get to the point where it can reliably put her in outfits other than what's in the dataset.
Still, it's not perfect - the default outfit has a tendency to sometimes bleed over, particularly the leotard. Use the relevant tag from above in negatives and/or lower the LoRA strength a bit to get rid of it.

I recommend DPM++ 2M Karras and LoRA at strength 0.8 for AOM2. NAI users will have better results with Euler A at the same strength.

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!
Like my LoRAs and want more? Please consider a small tip towards my electricity bill and further training >.<

MISC
Trained on NAI with a dataset of 45 images and a lot of foul language.

items.name: Infrared Photos
items.description:
Infrared photography involves capturing images using a portion of the light spectrum that is beyond what the human eye can perceive. Infrared light lies outside the range of visible light, with longer wavelengths.

In infrared photography, special camera equipment or filters are used to block out visible light while allowing infrared light to pass through. This results in a unique and distinct visual representation of the scene, with some colors appearing differently than they would in normal visible light photography.

The characteristics of infrared photography can vary depending on the specific technique or equipment used. In general, infrared photographs often exhibit certain key features:

1. Increased Contrast: Infrared photography tends to produce images with heightened contrast, as infrared light interacts differently with various surfaces, resulting in distinct tonal variations.

2. Ethereal and Dreamlike Atmosphere: Infrared images often have a surreal and ethereal quality, with foliage appearing white or light-colored, creating a ghostly effect. Skies can appear darker, and clouds may have a dramatic contrast against the background.

3. Invisible Infrared Light Sources: Infrared photography can reveal light sources that are typically invisible to the human eye, such as heat radiation or infrared reflections.

4. Creative Effects: Infrared photography opens up possibilities for creative experimentation, as it can transform ordinary scenes into otherworldly landscapes or add a unique twist to portraiture.

Infrared photography finds various applications, including landscape photography, architectural photography, and even scientific and forensic investigations.

It's important to note that capturing infrared photographs requires specialized equipment or modifications to conventional cameras. Additionally, post-processing techniques may be employed to enhance or fine-tune the final images.

Infrared photography offers a fascinating and captivating way to explore and interpret the world around us, revealing unseen aspects and presenting scenes in a fresh and intriguing light.

items.name: Nanahira LoRA
items.description:
CC License

A LoRA of the cute voiced utaite Nanahira but her vtuber form

This LoRA was made with a collection of fanart images I could find of her online, she has a lot of finer details that might need you to do cherry picking when looking at specific outputs (like her single thighhigh having the correct stripe pattern or the cross lace) but otherwise I am quite satisfied and just happy to make a LORA of one of my fave Japanese musicians

Recommended Weight

Always 1.0 by itself and 0.8-0.7 if you're mixing it with other LORAs.

Compatibility

Trained on the NAI model, so it's pretty much compatible with every NAI based Anime model mix that you can find on the internet

Trigger Tokens

"nanahi" will be the trigger token you use along with these general tags to be used as the activation tokens

"light brown hair, long hair, blunt bangs, bangs, green ribbon, hair ribbon, yellow eyes, green jacket, white dress, open jacket, criss-cross halter, halterneck, black choker, x hair ornament, hairclip, single thighhigh, striped thighhigh, bow "

and if you want to put her into different outfits or hairstyles don't use the "nanahi" trigger token and just up the strength on the individual outfits/hairstyle you want in the positive prompts and you can get them "most of the time", there wasn't enough art for the "althira" tag that I made to see if it helped with alternative outfits/looks but honestly just try it out along with putting "halterneck/criss-cross halter/choker/black choker" into the negatives, these aspects of her outfit may bleed in but otherwise just remember the common tags for her regular look and you'll get by

Support

As always if you want to support me in my LORA making endeavors just check out one of my platforms, Pixiv and Twitter for my posted works while Ko-Fi/Fiverr can be visited to support me financially, thanks a lot if you support me in any way o/
